.TH SGDRM-DESCRIBE 1 "2026-05-07" "SGUTILS 2.0.0" "Screen Graphics Utilities"
.SH NAME
sgdrm-describe \- describe DRM/KMS display outputs
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B sgdrm-describe
[\fB-d\fR \fIDEVICE\fR] [\fB-j\fR] [\fB--help\fR]
.SH DESCRIPTION
.B sgdrm-describe
lists all connected DRM/KMS display outputs, showing connector names,
resolutions, refresh rates, and the driver in use.
.SH OPTIONS
.TP
.BR -d ", " --device " " \fIPATH\fR
DRM device path (default: /dev/dri/card0).
.TP
.BR -j ", " --json
Output as JSON array.
.TP
.BR -h ", " --help
Show help message.
.TP
.BR -v ", " --version
Show version.
.SH EXAMPLES
.nf
$ sgdrm-describe
HDMI-A-1 1920x1080@60Hz (driver: i915)

$ sgdrm-describe --json
[{"connector":"HDMI-A-1","width":1920,"height":1080,"refresh":60,"driver":"i915"}]

$ sgdrm-describe -d /dev/dri/card1
.fi
.SH SEE ALSO
.BR sgdrm-clear (1),
.BR sgfb-describe (1)

